SUMMARY:Saturday in the Octave of Easter
DESCRIPTION:Rank: Weekday\nLiturgical color: white\nSeason: Easter\nReading
 s: Acts 4:13-21/Mk 16:9-15 (266) Pss Prop 9 Nine readings are assigned to
  the Easter Vigil: seven from the Old Testament and two from the New. If 
 circumstances demand in individual cases\, the number of prescribed readi
 ngs may be reduced. Three selections from the Old Testament\, both from t
 he Law and Prophets\, should be read before the Epistle and Gospel. In an
 y case\, the reading from Exodus about the escape through the Red Sea (re
 ading 3) should never be omitted. celebrated as Solemnities of the Lord
 ” (Universal Norms on the Liturgical Year and the Calendar\, no. 24).\n
 Source: USCCB Liturgical Calendar PDF (https://www.usccb.org/resources/20
 27cal.pdf)\nVerify local observances with your diocese or parish.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
