SUMMARY:Easter Weekday
DESCRIPTION:Rank: Weekday\nLiturgical color: white\, red\nSeason: Easter\nO
 ptional observance(s): Saint Fidelis of Sigmaringen\, Priest and Martyr\n
 Readings: Acts 4:23-31/Jn 3:1-8 (267) Pss II 11 Nine readings are assigne
 d to the Easter Vigil: seven from the Old Testament and two from the New.
  If circumstances demand in individual cases\, the number of prescribed r
 eadings may be reduced. Three selections from the Old Testament\, both fr
 om the Law and Prophets\, should be read before the Epistle and Gospel. I
 n any case\, the reading from Exodus about the escape through the Red Sea
  (reading 3) should never be omitted. celebrated as Solemnities of the Lo
 rd” (Universal Norms on the Liturgical Year and the Calendar\, no. 24).
 \nSource: USCCB Liturgical Calendar PDF (https://www.usccb.org/resources/
 2028cal.pdf)\nVerify local observances with your diocese or parish.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
